<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-12-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="12" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                    <head>12. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_NGA1" type="from">Nasser</persName> to President <persName type="to">Johnson</persName><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d12fn1">Source:
                            Johnson Library, National Security File, Country File, United Arab
                            Republic, Vol. VI, Memos, 8/67–7/68. No classification marking. The
                            letter was delivered to President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> by <persName>James Birdsall</persName> on
                            December 18; see <ref target="#d21">Document 21</ref>.</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>Cairo</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1967-12-09">December 9, 1967</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Dear Mr. President:</p>
                    <p>I take this opportunity to extend my best wishes to you and your family.</p>
                    <p>At this time which is sacred to both our people I feel that good relations
                        should exist between our people.</p>
                    <p>I have sent a special message through Mr. <persName>Birdsall</persName>. I
                        trust you will receive it in the spirit which I send it.</p>
                    <p>With highest personal regards.</p>
                    <p>Sincerely,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName>
                                <hi rend="strong">Jamal Abdul Nasser</hi>
                            </persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>